The first passenger train from Nakuru to Kisumu is slated for November 2021. Rehabilitation works on the Nakuru-Kisumu-Busia metre gauge railway line will be complete in the next two weeks. Speaking at fort tenan after an inspection tour of the mgr line, Kenya Railways managing director, Philip mainga said Kenya railways will conduct a test run in two weeks time. a section of the line in miwani had been vandalised but the stakeholders issued a warning indicating anyone found guilty will face the full force of the law.